The Administration shall disqualify any individual from driving a commercial motor vehicle for a period of 1 year if:
The individual is convicted of committing any of the following offenses while driving a commercial motor vehicle:
A violation of § 21-902 of this article;
A violation of a federal law or any other state's law which is substantially similar in nature to the provisions in § 21-902 of this article;
Leaving the scene of an accident which requires disqualification as provided by the United States Secretary of Transportation;
A crime, other than a crime described in subsection (e) of this section, that is punishable by death or imprisonment for a term exceeding 1 year;
A violation of § 25-112 of this article; or
A violation of § 2-209, § 2-503, § 2-504, § 2-505, or § 2-506 of the Criminal Law Article.
The individual holds a commercial driver's license and is convicted of committing any of the following offenses while driving a noncommercial motor vehicle:
A violation of § 21-902(a), (c), or (d) of this article;
A violation of a federal law or any other state's law which is substantially similar in nature to the provisions in § 21-902(a), (c), or (d) of this article;
Leaving the scene of an accident which requires disqualification as provided by the United States Secretary of Transportation; or
A crime, other than a crime described in subsection (e) of this section, that is punishable by death or imprisonment for a term exceeding 1 year;
The individual, while driving a commercial motor vehicle or while holding a commercial driver's license, refuses to undergo testing as provided in § 16-205.1 of this title or as is required by any other state's law or by federal law in the enforcement of 49 C.F.R. § 383.51 Table 1, or 49 C.F.R. § 392.5(a)(2);
The individual drives or attempts to drive a commercial motor vehicle while the alcohol concentration of the person's blood or breath is 0.04 or greater; or
The individual drives a commercial motor vehicle when, as a result of prior violations committed while driving a commercial motor vehicle, the driver's commercial driver's license is revoked, suspended, or canceled or the driver is disqualified from driving a commercial motor vehicle.

section.section:
The Administration shall issue a commercial driver's license to the applicant when the applicant:
Passes the skills and knowledge tests required by this subtitle;
Is eligible to drive pursuant to the Commercial Driver's License Information System, and National Driver's Register;
Surrenders any previously issued driver's instructional permit or license; and
Pays the fees required by § 16-818(a)(1) of this subtitle.
